Create a class named Country with the following member variables/attributes
 

Variable          

 Datatype

name

 String 

countryCode     

 String 

isdCode

 String

Create another class and write the main method to test the above class.

 

[Note :

Strictly adhere to the object-oriented specifications are given as a part of the problem statement.

Use the same class names, attribute names, and method names.]

 

Input Format:

First-line contains Country Name

the second line contains Country Code

The next line contains ISD code 

Output Format:

 Refer to sample output for formatting specifications.

 

Sample Input:

India

IND

91

Sample Output:

Country Name : India

Country Code : IND

ISD Code : 91


-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------

solution:-

import java.util.Scanner;
class country{
    static String name;
    static String countryCode;
    static String isdCode;
    static{
        Scanner scan = new Scanner(System.in);
        name=scan.next();
        countryCode=scan.next();
        isdCode=scan.next();
    }
    
}
class Solution extends country{
    public static void main(String[] args){
        
        System.out.println("Country Name : "+ name);
        System.out.println("Country Code :"+ countryCode);
        System.out.println("ISD Code : "+ isdCode);
    }
}
